    • Enum Constant Detail

      • AdServingOptimizationStatus

        public static final CampaignField AdServingOptimizationStatus
        Ad serving optimization status.

      • AdvertisingChannelSubType

        public static final CampaignField AdvertisingChannelSubType
        Optional refinement of advertisingChannelType. Must be a valid sub-type of the parent channel type. May only be set for new campaigns and cannot be changed once set.

      • AdvertisingChannelType

        public static final CampaignField AdvertisingChannelType
        The primary serving target for ads within this campaign. The targeting options can be refined in NetworkSetting. May only be set for new campaigns. This field is required and should not be null when it is contained within Operators : ADD

      • Amount

        public static final CampaignField Amount
        Amount of budget in the local currency for the account.

      • BidCeiling

        public static final CampaignField BidCeiling
        Ceiling on bids placed by the budget optimizer.

      • BidType

        public static final CampaignField BidType
        Bid type indicates if it is a Target CPA campaign. If the Bid type is not specified it defaults to Target CPA.

      • BiddingStrategyId

        public static final CampaignField BiddingStrategyId
        Id of the bidding strategy to be associated with the campaign, ad group or ad group criteria. A bidding strategy is created using the BiddingStrategyService ADD operation and is assigned a BiddingStrategyId. The BiddingStrategyId can be shared across campaigns, ad groups and ad group criteria.

      • BiddingStrategyName

        public static final CampaignField BiddingStrategyName
        Name of the bidding strategy. This is applicable only for flexible bidding strategies.

      • BiddingStrategyType

        public static final CampaignField BiddingStrategyType
        The type of the bidding strategy to be attached.

      • BudgetId

        public static final CampaignField BudgetId
        A Budget is created using the BudgetService ADD operation and is assigned a BudgetId. The BudgetId is used when modifying the Budget with BudgetService, or associating the Budget to a Campaign with CampaignService. A BudgetId can be shared across different campaigns--the system will then allocate the Budget among the Campaigns to get the optimum result.

      • BudgetName

        public static final CampaignField BudgetName
        Name of the Budget. When creating a Budget through BudgetService, every explicitly shared Budget must have a non-null non-empty name. In addition, all explicitly shared Budget names owned by an account must be distinct. Budgets that are not explicitly shared derive their name from the attached Campaign's name.

      • BudgetReferenceCount

        public static final CampaignField BudgetReferenceCount
        Number of campaigns actively using this budget. This field is only populated for Get operations.

      • BudgetStatus

        public static final CampaignField BudgetStatus

      • DeliveryMethod

        public static final CampaignField DeliveryMethod
        Delivery method for the Budget which determines the rate at which the Budget is spent. Defaults to STANDARD and can be changed through BudgetService ADD or SET operations.

      • Eligible

        public static final CampaignField Eligible
        If the campaign is eligible to enter conversion optimizer.

      • EndDate

        public static final CampaignField EndDate
        Date the campaign ends. On add, defaults to 20371230, which means the campaign will run indefinitely. To set an existing campaign to run indefinitely, set this field to 20371230. The date's format should be YYYYMMDD.

      • EnhancedCpcEnabled

        public static final CampaignField EnhancedCpcEnabled
        The enhanced CPC bidding option for the campaign, which enables bids to be enhanced based on conversion optimizer data. For more information about enhanced CPC, see the AdWords Help Center.

      • FrequencyCapMaxImpressions

        public static final CampaignField FrequencyCapMaxImpressions
        Maximum number of impressions allowed during the time range by this cap. To remove the frequency cap on a campaign, set this field to 0.

      • Id

        public static final CampaignField Id
        ID of this campaign.

      • IsBudgetExplicitlyShared

        public static final CampaignField IsBudgetExplicitlyShared
        If true, this budget was created with the purpose of sharing this budget across one or more campaigns.

        If false, this budget was created with the intention to be dedicatedly used with a single campaign, and the Budget's name and status will stay in the sync with the associated Campaign's name and status. Attempting to share this budget with a second Campaign will result in an error.

      • Labels

        public static final CampaignField Labels
        Labels that are attached to the campaign. To associate an existing Label to an existing Campaign, use CampaignService#mutateLabel with the ADD operator. To remove an associated Label from the Campaign, use CampaignService#mutateLabel with the REMOVE operator. To filter on Labels, use one of Predicate.Operator#CONTAINS_ALL, Predicate.Operator#CONTAINS_ANY, Predicate.Operator#CONTAINS_NONE operators with a list of Label ids.

      • Level

        public static final CampaignField Level
        The level on which the cap is to be applied (creative/adgroup). Cap is applied to all the entities of this level in the campaign.

      • Name

        public static final CampaignField Name
        Name of this campaign. This field is required and should not be null for ADD operations. For SET and REMOVE operations, this can be used to address the campaign by name when the campaign is ENABLED or PAUSED. Removed campaigns cannot be addressed by name. If you wish to rename a campaign, you must provide the ID.

      • Period

        public static final CampaignField Period
        Period over which to spend the budget. Defaults to DAILY when creating a Budget through BudgetService. MONTHLY is not available to most users.

      • PricingMode

        public static final CampaignField PricingMode
        Note: The value for this field currently cannot be changed. Pricing model indicates whether it is a pay per clicks or pay per conversions campaign. If the pricing model is not specified it defaults to Clicks.

      • RejectionReasons

        public static final CampaignField RejectionReasons
        Reason why a campaign would be rejected for conversion optimizer.

      • ServingStatus

        public static final CampaignField ServingStatus
        Serving status.

      • Settings

        public static final CampaignField Settings
        List of settings for the campaign.

      • StartDate

        public static final CampaignField StartDate
        Date the campaign begins. On add, defaults to the current day in the parent account's local timezone. The date's format should be YYYYMMDD.

      • Status

        public static final CampaignField Status
        Status of this campaign. On add, defaults to ENABLED.

      • TargetContentNetwork

        public static final CampaignField TargetContentNetwork
        Ads will be served on specified placements in the Google Display Network. Placements are specified using Placement criteria.

      • TargetCpa

        public static final CampaignField TargetCpa
        Average CPA target. This target should be greater than or equal to minimum billable unit based on the currency for the account.

      • TargetCpaMaxCpcBidCeiling

        public static final CampaignField TargetCpaMaxCpcBidCeiling
        Maximum cpc bid limit that applies to all keywords managed by the strategy.

      • TargetCpaMaxCpcBidFloor

        public static final CampaignField TargetCpaMaxCpcBidFloor
        Minimum cpc bid limit that applies to all keywords managed by the strategy.

      • TargetGoogleSearch

        public static final CampaignField TargetGoogleSearch
        Ads will be served with Google.com search results.

      • TargetPartnerSearchNetwork

        public static final CampaignField TargetPartnerSearchNetwork
        Ads will be served on the Google Partner Network. This is available to only some specific Google partner accounts.

      • TargetRoas

        public static final CampaignField TargetRoas
        The desired revenue (based on conversion data) per unit of spend.

      • TargetRoasBidCeiling

        public static final CampaignField TargetRoasBidCeiling
        Maximum bid limit that applies to all keywords managed by the strategy.

      • TargetRoasBidFloor

        public static final CampaignField TargetRoasBidFloor
        Minimum bid limit that applies to all keywords managed by the strategy.

      • TargetSearchNetwork

        public static final CampaignField TargetSearchNetwork
        Ads will be served on partner sites in the Google Search Network (requires GOOGLE_SEARCH).

      • TargetSpendBidCeiling

        public static final CampaignField TargetSpendBidCeiling
        The largest max CPC bid that can be set by the TargetSpend bidder.

      • TargetSpendSpendTarget

        public static final CampaignField TargetSpendSpendTarget
        A spend target under which to maximize clicks. The TargetSpend bidder will attempt to spend the smaller of this value or the natural throttling spend amount. If not specified, the budget is used as the spend target.

      • TimeUnit

        public static final CampaignField TimeUnit
        Unit of time the cap is defined at. Only the Day, Week and Month time units are supported.

      • TrackingUrlTemplate

        public static final CampaignField TrackingUrlTemplate
        URL template for constructing a tracking URL.

        On update, empty string ("") indicates to clear the field.

      • UrlCustomParameters

        public static final CampaignField UrlCustomParameters
        A list of mappings to be used for substituting URL custom parameter tags in the trackingUrlTemplate, finalUrls, and/or finalMobileUrls.
